00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:17.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I was taught growing up
that in order to be successful

00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:21.220 align:middle line:90%
in life, you had to try hard.

00:00:21.220 --> 00:00:25.350 align:middle line:84%
You had to be faster,
smarter, better, that there

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:28.650 align:middle line:84%
was a lot of scarcity in the
world, a lot of limitation,

00:00:28.650 --> 00:00:32.369 align:middle line:84%
a lot of suffering, that
you could be kicked out

00:00:32.369 --> 00:00:34.350 align:middle line:84%
of your house, not
have enough to eat,

00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:37.930 align:middle line:84%
lose everything if you
weren't on top of it,

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:40.000 align:middle line:84%
if you didn't have a
really good education,

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.920 align:middle line:84%
and if you didn't work
really, really hard,

00:00:43.920 --> 00:00:46.890 align:middle line:90%
and really basically struggle.

00:00:46.890 --> 00:00:51.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Some of the background
or story that I lived with

00:00:51.090 --> 00:00:57.240 align:middle line:84%
and come from has to do with
early childhood and moving from

00:00:57.240 --> 00:00:59.850 align:middle line:84%
Israel, where I was born, and
learned how to speak Hebrew,

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:03.790 align:middle line:84%
and went to kindergarten, and
then being moved from Israel,

00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:05.800 align:middle line:84%
where I had my comfort
zone, to Montreal,

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:10.260 align:middle line:84%
Canada and put in grade one,
not understanding the French

00:01:10.260 --> 00:01:14.380 align:middle line:84%
